# .nvmrc — Node version pin for Flightplan
#
# Tells nvm which Node version to use for this project.
# Developers with nvm installed run: nvm use
# nvm will automatically switch to Node 20 LTS.
#
# Why Node 20:
#   better-sqlite3 and sqlite-vec publish pre-built binaries for Node 18–22.
#   Node 23+ requires compiling from source, which hits C++20 toolchain
#   requirements that are not reliably present on all developer machines.
#   Node 20 is the current LTS (Long Term Support) release — stable,
#   well-supported, and what production deployments use.
#
# If you see "zsh: command not found: nvm", install nvm first:
#   curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
#   Then close and reopen Terminal, then run: nvm use
20
